00:29:09,334 --> 00:29:11,754
Behold...the one who failed.

310
00:29:12,719 --> 00:29:14,507
 Still trying to win the bet?

311
00:29:15,819 --> 00:29:17,344
I didn't even open the bottle.

312
00:29:18,023 --> 00:29:19,591
 Honey, it's all yours.

313
00:29:21,544 --> 00:29:23,858
He said you were mine.

314
00:30:16,006 --> 00:30:20,933
 Hey, don't you want to dance?
 I dance really well.

315
00:30:24,001 --> 00:30:26,367
I don't know, it's too crowded.

316
00:30:27,474 --> 00:30:29,534
 Hey!
What's wrong with you?

317
00:30:30,649 --> 00:30:33,602
It looks like I'm poison!

318
00:30:35,064 --> 00:30:37,442
You are not the poison, I am.

319
00:30:39,741 --> 00:30:41,830
Here, my share, I'm leaving.

320
00:30:53,953 --> 00:30:57,818
Lieutenant, I've been wanting to talk to you
I've been wanting to talk to you...

321
00:30:58,337 --> 00:31:00,680
Here, I'm sorry.

322
00:31:03,509 --> 00:31:04,910
Are you inviting me to sit down?

323
00:31:08,133 --> 00:31:09,255
 Thank you.

324
00:31:11,216 --> 00:31:13,314
I think we have
things to say to each other.

325
00:31:14,079 --> 00:31:15,935
 - No doubt that....
- I invite you to dinner?

326
00:31:16,606 --> 00:31:19,152
I don't know,
Los Angeles is going to be a tough day.

327
00:31:19,536 --> 00:31:22,166
Lockheed, Douglas, the shipyard...

328
00:31:22,480 --> 00:31:23,810
We'll have to eat!

329
00:31:24,272 --> 00:31:26,223
It's very nice of you to
to take care of my health!

330
00:31:26,427 --> 00:31:27,731
Just a suggestion.

331
00:31:30,445 --> 00:31:32,606
So, a nightclub and
a few dance steps?

332
00:31:32,822 --> 00:31:34,443
 Come on, you deserve this.

333
00:31:34,722 --> 00:31:37,259
You really have the
in the ideas!

334
00:31:37,284 --> 00:31:39,067
 I have no interest in giving up.

335
00:31:41,049 --> 00:31:43,503
Okay. But no nightclub.

336
00:31:43,871 --> 00:31:45,786
Dinner and a movie, right?

337
00:31:47,823 --> 00:31:50,168
I think I have no
strength of character!

338
00:31:51,002 --> 00:31:52,295
I'll be right back.

339
00:33:33,748 --> 00:33:37,047
All he wants is to finish
this bottle and three others

340
00:33:37,072 --> 00:33:40,141
and water his garden with champagne
rather than the Germans drinking it.

341
00:33:40,258 --> 00:33:43,619
That should make us feel better about the occupation,
isn't it, Mr. Ricky?

342
00:33:43,850 --> 00:33:45,052
You said it.

343
00:33:45,265 --> 00:33:46,952
They're looking at you, kid.

344
00:34:10,172 --> 00:34:13,534
A beautiful song, but
sad like the movie.

345
00:34:15,485 --> 00:34:18,097
Why does everything that is
beautiful must be sad?

346
00:34:18,481 --> 00:34:19,526
Not always.

347
00:34:22,599 --> 00:34:24,710
I wonder who
you really are.

348
00:34:25,360 --> 00:34:27,959
Your past. What you used to say?
What you were thinking?

349
00:34:28,210 --> 00:34:29,475
No questions asked.

350
00:34:30,946 --> 00:34:32,842
It is not forbidden to try to guess.

351
00:34:33,031 --> 00:34:34,296
 Guess what?

352
00:34:34,665 --> 00:34:36,858
Why hasn't anyone been there since.

353
00:34:37,067 --> 00:34:38,393
 Since "Arizona"?

354
00:34:39,016 --> 00:34:40,805
You can say it, it's in the past.

355
00:34:40,915 --> 00:34:42,010
So?

356
00:34:42,707 --> 00:34:44,374
I won't let that happen again.

357
00:34:45,261 --> 00:34:46,600
 What are you afraid of?

358
00:34:47,366 --> 00:34:49,002
Men who may die tomorrow.

359
00:34:49,694 --> 00:34:52,241
Things that need to be finished before
end before they begin.

360
00:34:53,966 --> 00:34:56,780
What else?
What would you like?

361
00:34:57,077 --> 00:34:59,284
Oh, a nice man with a few dollars,

362
00:34:59,769 --> 00:35:01,805
 or a reformed one that is more or less intact.

363
00:35:02,220 --> 00:35:03,327
Someone sure.

364
00:35:03,613 --> 00:35:04,802
It could be me.

365
00:35:06,822 --> 00:35:08,045
The war is not over.

366
00:35:09,261 --> 00:35:10,594
 For me, yes.

367
00:35:11,383 --> 00:35:13,397
I am a veteran by decree.

368
00:35:13,979 --> 00:35:16,171
I am labeled:
"Hero, handle with care".

369
00:35:16,773 --> 00:35:18,778
You never know what
what will happen tomorrow.

370
00:35:20,349 --> 00:35:22,318
I know what's going on here tonight.

371
00:35:23,386 --> 00:35:25,445
For me... for us.

372
00:35:27,037 --> 00:35:28,795
No, please.

373
00:35:33,073 --> 00:35:35,225
It is also something
you learn in the army...

374
00:35:35,888 --> 00:35:36,982
To be expected.

375
00:35:46,554 --> 00:35:47,561
Allow me.

376
00:35:55,508 --> 00:35:57,420
- Well, good night.
- Thank you.

377
00:35:58,027 --> 00:36:01,125
Jack. Would you like to come in
for a nightcap?

378
00:36:01,949 --> 00:36:03,298
You are forcing my hand!

379
00:36:08,529 --> 00:36:11,431
I keep a bottle for
midnight visitors.

380
00:36:21,869 --> 00:36:23,251
Is it for dwarfs?

381
00:36:24,172 --> 00:36:26,930
You're lucky that
I kept this from the train

382
00:36:35,316 --> 00:36:36,542
I feel like a chemist.

383
00:36:44,762 --> 00:36:46,464
 They're looking at you, kid.

384
00:36:58,626 --> 00:36:59,863
- No. Why not?
- Why not?

385
00:36:59,962 --> 00:37:01,191
I told you.

386
00:37:01,277 --> 00:37:03,027
Why?
Is it against the rules?

387
00:37:03,392 --> 00:37:05,096
You can't be serious. It's just...

388
00:37:05,121 --> 00:37:06,183
 Just what?

389
00:37:07,782 --> 00:37:09,145
You want me there.

390
00:37:09,170 --> 00:37:10,903
 Of course, but that's not all.

391
00:37:12,629 --> 00:37:14,386
 I have nothing else.

392
00:37:14,737 --> 00:37:17,107
You are everything I want,
all I need

393
00:37:17,699 --> 00:37:18,908
 Peggy, I love you.

394
00:37:19,018 --> 00:37:20,222
 I want you to be my wife.

395
00:37:27,206 --> 00:37:28,340
I'm afraid.

396
00:37:33,850 --> 00:37:37,078
You shouldn't be afraid,
that's what I'm trying to tell you.

397
00:37:38,341 --> 00:37:41,366
I am here with you and
I will always be here.

398
00:37:44,725 --> 00:37:46,098
 Peggy, love me!

399
00:37:47,072 --> 00:37:48,545
 Love me as I love you.

400
00:37:49,829 --> 00:37:52,288
I love you that's why I'm afraid.

401
00:38:23,107 --> 00:38:25,013
I owe you $50!

402
00:39:09,319 --> 00:39:10,811
 How long will it last?

403
00:39:10,836 --> 00:39:12,889
Until I get older
and you get fat.

404
00:39:29,899 --> 00:39:30,938
 What is it?

405
00:39:31,453 --> 00:39:32,766
It's from headquarters.

406
00:39:33,289 --> 00:39:34,367
 Jack!

407
00:39:34,758 --> 00:39:36,680
Orders, that couldn't last forever.
last forever.

408
00:39:37,617 --> 00:39:41,110
They want to keep me in New York,
but it won't always be permanent.

409
00:39:45,929 --> 00:39:48,369
Go on your own to Camp Pendleton.
to Camp Pendleton.

410
00:39:48,666 --> 00:39:50,638
Report to Colonel A.J. Baseman.

411
00:39:50,872 --> 00:39:52,224
He's my former commander.

412
00:39:52,443 --> 00:39:56,146
 Commander of the 1st Battalion
Marines and await orders.

413
00:39:56,511 --> 00:39:57,677
What are you going to do?

414
00:39:58,412 --> 00:40:00,655
Train the marines, I guess.

415
00:40:01,753 --> 00:40:03,186
Won't you get on board?

416
00:40:04,450 --> 00:40:06,046
 Good, steady work.

417
00:40:07,652 --> 00:40:11,319
From now on, we are part of the
are part of the garrison.

418
00:40:11,480 --> 00:40:14,183
We will have a small
house, a kind of duplex

419
00:40:14,208 --> 00:40:15,671
We will live on the base.

420
00:40:15,995 --> 00:40:17,374
I know you'll like it, Peggy.

421
00:40:17,912 --> 00:40:19,190
 I love you.

422
00:40:19,628 --> 00:40:21,254
I love you so much!

423
00:40:21,905 --> 00:40:23,741
If anything should happen to you...

424
00:40:23,957 --> 00:40:25,311
 Not today, not tomorrow,

425
00:40:25,552 --> 00:40:26,819
never.

426
00:40:39,080 --> 00:40:41,965
 - Hello Lieutenant Connell.
- Good to see you, Colonel.

427
00:40:41,990 --> 00:40:43,682
 - Welcome to Pendleton.
- Thank you, sir.

428
00:40:43,707 --> 00:40:45,665
You look good, healthy
in good health.

429
00:40:45,690 --> 00:40:47,884
Does marriage work for you?

430
00:40:48,048 --> 00:40:49,688
Are you already installed?

431
00:40:49,756 --> 00:40:50,866
 Like birds in the nest.

432
00:40:51,101 --> 00:40:53,775
Good, good, then we can
get to work.

433
00:40:54,572 --> 00:40:57,447
Colonel, what was the situation like
when you left the guys?

434
00:40:57,734 --> 00:40:59,749
Difficult, the men were exhausted.

435
00:40:59,774 --> 00:41:01,384
The army finally came to relieve them

436
00:41:01,409 --> 00:41:03,883
and everyone went to
rest in New Zealand

437
00:41:04,882 --> 00:41:06,418
Did you get to see Ed Carnavan?

438
00:41:06,991 --> 00:41:10,119
Yes, I wanted to see it.

439
00:41:11,158 --> 00:41:13,724
He asked me to
to tell you not to come back.

440
00:41:13,749 --> 00:41:15,022
 There is a problem.

441
00:41:16,545 --> 00:41:19,428
He tries to drink all
the sake by himself.

442
00:41:20,517 --> 00:41:22,421
 It's a good marine, the best.

443
00:41:23,048 --> 00:41:24,165
Yes, that's right,

444
00:41:24,190 --> 00:41:26,509
 all hands on deck
when we go ashore.

445
00:41:27,132 --> 00:41:28,675
They don't miss anything, do they?

446
00:41:29,682 --> 00:41:30,968
Do you want to come back with them?

447
00:41:31,659 --> 00:41:34,753
No sir, I am happily married.

