471
00:42:38,506 --> 00:42:40,120
 - You'll regret it.
- I know you will.

472
00:42:40,145 --> 00:42:42,325
You will all have the opportunity
to get to know each other better.

473
00:42:42,350 --> 00:42:44,583
Our table is over there.

474
00:42:44,608 --> 00:42:46,883
Excuse me, would you like to follow me?

475
00:42:46,908 --> 00:42:48,258
 - Welcome aboard.
 - Thank you for your time.

476
00:42:49,033 --> 00:42:52,376
Gentlemen, what if we put
the pretty girl here, in the middle.

477
00:42:52,449 --> 00:42:53,571
Here.

478
00:42:58,159 --> 00:42:59,463
What would you like to drink?

479
00:42:59,614 --> 00:43:03,468
 I recommend the Bourbon
or Rum, because that's all it has.

480
00:43:04,203 --> 00:43:07,088
Bourbon is fine and Peggy
takes it with water.

481
00:43:07,136 --> 00:43:08,518
Three Bourbons with water!

482
00:43:10,166 --> 00:43:12,040
I am curious to know

483
00:43:12,163 --> 00:43:13,739
this whole thing
of public heroes.

484
00:43:13,764 --> 00:43:16,146
So you're being taken on a tour?

485
00:43:16,945 --> 00:43:19,562
To tell you the truth, Colonel, I was
a little scared at first,

486
00:43:19,820 --> 00:43:21,218
 but that's what they wanted.

487
00:43:21,243 --> 00:43:22,874
 He sold many war bonds.

488
00:43:22,899 --> 00:43:26,360
There's no need to defend him, Ms. Connell,
what he did was important.

489
00:43:26,747 --> 00:43:30,476
Before, he was a good
sergeant with a bit of an attitude.

490
00:43:31,812 --> 00:43:34,436
Now he's a real movie star.

491
00:43:36,503 --> 00:43:38,726
I think you get used to everything, Colonel.

492
00:43:39,442 --> 00:43:40,759
Even to train recruits.

493
00:43:40,875 --> 00:43:43,951
No, don't minimize your work Jack.

494
00:43:44,230 --> 00:43:46,357
the training of men
here is important,

495
00:43:46,382 --> 00:43:48,401
and without these vouchers, we
we wouldn't have much.

496
00:43:49,189 --> 00:43:50,577
But you will have to leave early,

497
00:43:50,602 --> 00:43:53,374
tomorrow morning, he should be
with his group at 6am sharp.

498
00:43:53,754 --> 00:43:57,124
Oh, you don't waste time!
Are you married Colonel?

499
00:43:57,440 --> 00:44:01,716
Yes..., I'm married.
 My wife is in Virginia,

500
00:44:02,702 --> 00:44:03,986
 in Quantico.

501
00:44:04,321 --> 00:44:07,232
Do you disapprove of officers
having their wives near them?

502
00:44:07,654 --> 00:44:10,294
 Well I...  I approve of your presence.

503
00:44:11,256 --> 00:44:15,380
I think it will be a great help.

504
00:44:20,635 --> 00:44:22,997
To a new Marine wife

