01:31:20,177 --> 01:31:22,216
Let's go !
With me!

1022
01:31:22,224 --> 01:31:23,224
Bazooka!

1023
01:32:27,787 --> 01:32:29,325
- You got it.
- Rockets

1024
01:32:42,389 --> 01:32:43,869
Ammunition!

1025
01:32:58,174 --> 01:33:00,826
 Let's blow them up!
Cover us.

1026
01:33:08,713 --> 01:33:12,291
 We'll keep them busy.
 You'll both go.

1027
01:33:12,354 --> 01:33:13,806
You two come with me!

1028
01:33:13,855 --> 01:33:15,986
Let's get up there.
Let's go!

1029
01:33:34,229 --> 01:33:37,981
Hey! Attention, cease fire!

1030
01:34:00,303 --> 01:34:03,243
Hey....., he did it, let's go!

1031
01:34:09,965 --> 01:34:12,395
- Are you whole?
- I think so.

1032
01:34:15,763 --> 01:34:18,576
What do you want us to do now
do now, sir?

1033
01:34:23,403 --> 01:34:26,226
Secure the ridge,
put a team of shooters on it.

1034
01:34:26,469 --> 01:34:29,648
Okay, sir.
You heard the lieutenant.

1035
01:34:44,899 --> 01:34:46,874
 Hey!
Here you are.

1036
01:34:47,108 --> 01:34:49,498
- How is it going?
- Like a hole in the back.

1037
01:34:51,592 --> 01:34:53,053
Did they do well?

1038
01:34:53,545 --> 01:34:54,800
They were very good.

1039
01:34:55,029 --> 01:34:57,545
You and I can
make a great platoon.

1040
01:34:57,662 --> 01:34:59,004
Can be good.

1041
01:35:00,355 --> 01:35:01,967
What happened to you...

1042
01:35:03,514 --> 01:35:06,604
As you said:
 at Guadalcanal I was alone

1043
01:35:07,006 --> 01:35:09,525
now I have Peggy,
I didn't want her to lose me.

1044
01:35:10,780 --> 01:35:13,608
Okay, good thinking.

1045
01:35:14,068 --> 01:35:16,904
Keep it up and you'll be living
for many years.

1046
01:35:17,464 --> 01:35:21,842
He deserves the decoration the one who
was afraid, but did it anyway.

1047
01:35:23,703 --> 01:35:25,240
 Lieutenant Connell?

1048
01:35:26,277 --> 01:35:28,647
Captain Mason wants you
on the other side of the ridge.

1049
01:35:28,944 --> 01:35:30,615
It's bad out there.

1050
01:35:31,099 --> 01:35:33,295
- I'll go there immediately.
- Okay, sir.

1051
01:35:35,006 --> 01:35:38,443
All right guys,
get ready, we're moving!

1052
01:35:40,091 --> 01:35:41,526
"Short war" Lieutenant!

1053
01:35:43,045 --> 01:35:44,475
 "Short War" Gunny.

1054
01:35:44,842 --> 01:35:45,942
 Shanghai...

1055
01:35:50,686 --> 01:35:51,686
Are you afraid?

1056
01:35:53,373 --> 01:35:54,821
Of course I do!

1057
01:36:00,403 --> 01:36:03,232
Come on guys, come on!

1058
01:36:10,328 --> 01:36:11,948
And beyond this ridge,

1059
01:36:11,973 --> 01:36:14,005
 Saipan is waiting to be released.

1060
01:36:14,176 --> 01:36:17,629
 Then Tinian, Guam, Iwo Jima, Okinawa,

1061
01:36:17,708 --> 01:36:20,113
soon sinister and bloody names...

1062
01:36:20,270 --> 01:36:23,160
Some men will come back
and some will not.

1063
01:36:23,471 --> 01:36:27,668
 But the Corps will continue to struggle at
other times for other problems,

1064
01:36:27,725 --> 01:36:30,228
 always ready when the nation calls,

1065
01:36:30,356 --> 01:36:33,207
 always faithful, proud to be the

1066
01:36:33,400 --> 01:36:35,227
 FIRST TO FIGHT.

1067
01:37:09,221 --> 01:37:12,265
